	<!-- FAQ -->
	<h3>FAQ:</h3>
	<ol>
	  <b><li>What is Tryango?</li></b>
	  <p>Tryango is a secure e-mail encryption technique developed by the University of Birmingham (UK).</p>

	  <b><li>How do I install the Tryango Thunderbird plugin?</li></b>
	  <p>
		Download Tryango from the official website <a href="www.tryango.com">www.tryango.com</a>.<br><br>

		Open Thunderbird and go to Menu (the three stripes in the right upper corner)
		and select <i>Add-ons</i><br><br>

		In the Add-ons Manager click on the small cog in the right upper corner and
		select <i>Install Add-on From File...</i><br><br>

		Lastly, select the downloaded xpi-file of Tryango for your platform
		(e.g. tryango-0.9.3-linux-amd64.xpi) and restart Thunderbird.<br><br>

		The Tryango sign up dialog should now appear. If it does not show up, go to
		<i>Tryango</i> => <i>Sign-Up</i> in the menu bar.
	  </p>

	  <b><li>How do I sign up with Tryango?</li></b>
	  <p>
		Tryango should automatically show a sign up dialog upon first start up.
		If it does not, please  go to <i>Tryango</i> => <i>Sign-Up</i> in the menu bar.
	  </p>

	  <b><li>How do I send an encrypted e-mail with Tryango?</li></b>
	  <p>
		After signing up, Tryango should encrypt e-mails to other Tryango users by default.<br><br>
		In every e-mail composition window ("write new email"), these options can be temporarily
		changed via the Tryango menu.<br><br>

		The default options can be changed in <i>Tryango</i> => <i>Settings</i> but we recommend
		to encrypt/sign by default.<br><br>
	  </p>

	  <b><li>Where can I submit bugs?</li></b>
	  <p>Please submit bugs via github: <a href="https://github.com/tryango/tryango-client">
		  https://github.com/tryango/tryango-client</a>
	  </p>

	  <b><li>Who developed Tryango?</li></b>
      <p>Tryango is a project of the University of Birmingham (UK) and was developed by:
